        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 2:36AM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 235 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Roxboro, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail, heavy rainfall.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Roxboro, Concord, Bethel Hill, Mayo Reservoir, Hyco Lake, and John H
Kerr Reservoir.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
